name: exemplar
audience: public
description: >
  Reference implementation of the FOSS governance stack. Multi-stage
  code review pipeline with security, correctness, style, and
  architecture analysis. Full audit trails via Tessera hash-chain sealing.

domains:
  - governance-stack
  - code-review
  - policy-enforcement
  - auditing
  - reference-implementation

voice:
  tone: precise, integrative, governance-first
  principles:
    - Every review finding has severity, evidence, and remediation
    - Pipeline stages are independently testable
    - Audit trail is append-only and tamper-evident
    - Integrates all governance stack components as a reference
  anti-patterns:
    - Skipping stages in the review pipeline
    - Findings without evidence or remediation guidance
    - Tight coupling between review stages

standards:
  code_review:
    - Pact contracts for all component boundaries
    - Tessera sealing for audit artifacts
    - Chronicler events emitted at pipeline milestones
  documentation:
    - Integration points documented per governance component

connects_to:
  - pact
  - signet
  - tessera
  - sentinel
  - arbiter
  - chronicler
  - stigmergy
  - apprentice
  - kindex
  - ledger
  - cartographer
  - baton
  - constrain
  - agent-safe
  - blinddb
  - hermesp2p
